{"type":"item.completed","item":{"id":"item_61","type":"agent_message","text":"I’ve narrowed this down to a version-selection problem more than a raw “missing transport entry” problem. `netty-transport:4.2.1.Final` already ships its own native-image config, but the repo is still layering older `4.1.x` repo metadata from `netty-common`, `netty-buffer`, `netty-handler`, `netty-codec-http`, and others on top of the `4.2.1` jars.\n\nPlan:\n1. Add exact `4.2.1.Final` metadata entries for the Netty modules used by this test so the resolver stops falling back to older `4.1.x` metadata.\n2. Start those exact-version files minimal, leaning on the jars’ built-in native-image config where it already exists.\n3. Re-run `./gradlew test -Pcoordinates=io.netty:netty-transport:4.2.1.Final`.\n4. If the native test then reports actual missing registrations, add only those targeted entries instead of keeping the generated transport dump."}}
